==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Necrosis
<hw>Ne*cro"sis</hw> <pr>(n⟦esl⟧*kr⟦omac⟧"s⟦icr⟧s)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <grk>ne`krwsis</grk>, fr.
<grk>nekroy^n</grk> to make dead, to mortify, <grk>nekro`s</grk> a dead
body.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>The pathologic death of
part of a tissue due to irreversible damage. Contrast to
<contr>necrobiosis</contr>, which is a normal death of cells in a
tissue. Formerly, applied primarily to death of bone tissue.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A disease of trees, in which the
branches gradually dry up from the bark to the center.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Necrotic</ent>⟦br⟧
